Java class for IconStyleType complex type.

The following schema fragment specifies the expected content contained within this class. 


 <complexType name="IconStyleType">
   <complexContent>
     <extension base="{http://www.opengis.net/kml/2.2}AbstractColorStyleType">

    • getIconStyleSimpleExtensionGroups

      public List<Object> getIconStyleSimpleExtensionGroups()
      Gets the value of the iconStyleSimpleExtensionGroups property.

      This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the Jakarta XML Binding object. This is why there is not a set method for the iconStyleSimpleExtensionGroups property.

      For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

          getIconStyleSimpleExtensionGroups().add(newItem);

      Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list Object

      Returns:
      The value of the iconStyleSimpleExtensionGroups property.
